This is a bibliography of selected publications on the [[history of Chicago]]. For most topics, the easiest place to start is Janice L. Reiff, et al. eds. ''The Encyclopedia of Chicago'' (2004), which has thorough coverage by leading scholars in 1120pp of text and many illustrations. It does not include biographies. It is [http://www.encyclopedia.chicagohistory.org/ online free].
==Surveys== * Reiff, Janice L. Ann Durkin Keating and James R. Grossman, eds. ''The Encyclopedia of Chicago'' (2004) thorough coverage by scholars in 1120pp [http://www.encyclopedia.chicagohistory.org/ online free] * Abu-Lughod, Janet L. ''New York, Chicago, Los Angeles: America's Global Cities'' (U of Minnesota Press, 1999), Compares the three cities in terms of geography, economics and race from 1800 to 1990 * Andreas, A. T. ''History of Chicago. From the earliest period to the present time'' (1884) [https://archive.org/download/historyofchicago01andr/historyofchicago01andr_bw.pdf online v 1]; [https://archive.org/download/historyofchicago02andr/historyofchicago02andr_bw.pdf online v 2] ; [https://archive.org/download/historyofchicago03andruoft/historyofchicago03andruoft_bw.pdf online v. 3] * Gustaitis, Joseph. ''Chicago's Greatest Year, 1893: The White City and the Birth of a Modern Metropolis'' (2013) * Gustaitis, Joseph. ''Chicago Transformed: World War I and the Windy City'' (2016). * Longstreet, Stephen. ''Chicago: An Intimate Portrait of People, Pleasures, and Power, 1860-1919.'' (1973). 547 pp. popular * Miller, Donald L. ''City of the Century: The Epic of Chicago and the Making of America'' (1997), popular epic; [https://www.amazon.com/dp/0684831384/ excerpt and text search] * Pacyga, Dominic A. ''Chicago: A Biography'' (2011), 472pp; detailed history by a scholar, based on secondary sources. [https://www.amazon.com/gp/reader/0226644286/ excerpt and text search] *Pierce, Bessie Louise. ''A History of Chicago, Volume I: The Beginning of a City 1673-1848'' (1937; [https://www.amazon.com/History-Chicago-Beginning-City-1673-1848/dp/0226668398/ excerpt and text search vol 1]; ''Volume II: From Town to City 1848-1871'' (1940); ''Volume III: The Rise of a Modern City, 1871-1893'' (1957) ([https://www.amazon.com/History-Chicago-III-Modern-1871-1893/dp/0226668428/ excerpt and text search vol 3]; the major scholarly history * Sawyers, June Skinner. ''Chicago Portraits'' (2nd ed. Northwestern University Press, 2012), 250 short biographies * Spinney, Robert G. ''City of Big Shoulders: A History of Chicago'' (2000), popular epic; [https://www.amazon.com/dp/0875805833/ excerpt and text search]
