This is a list of '''University of Oxford people in the Law'''. Many were students at one (or more) of the [[Colleges of the University of Oxford|colleges]] of the University, and others held [[Fellow#Oxford, Cambridge and Dublin|fellowships]] at a college.
This list forms part of a series of lists of people associated with the University of Oxford &ndash; for other lists, please see the main article [[List of University of Oxford people]].
{{multiple image | align = right | direction = horizontal | width = | header = Lawyers who attended Oxford University | image1 = 1 David Neuberger, Baron Neuberger of Abbotsbury 2016.jpg | width1 = 129 | caption1 = [[Lord Neuberger]] | image2 = Ronald Dworkin at the Brooklyn Book Festival.jpg | width2 = 135 | caption2 = [[Ronald Dworkin]] | image3 = Elena Kagan Official SCOTUS Portrait (2013).jpg | width3 = 118 | caption3 = [[Elena Kagan]] }} Oxford has produced a large number of distinguished [[jurist]]s, [[judge]]s and [[lawyer]]s around the world. This list includes twelve [[Lord Chancellor]]s, ten [[Lord Chief Justice]]s, nine UK Supreme Court Justices and twenty-two [[law lord]]s; four associate justices of the [[US Supreme Court]] as well as six puisne justices of the [[Supreme Court of Canada]] and a chief justice of the now defunct [[Federal Court of Canada]]. The current [[Lord Chief Justice]] (the most senior judge in England and Wales), [[Ian Burnett, Baron Burnett of Maldon|Lord Burnett]], was educated at Oxford.
