ers]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | New Zealand | align="center" | Supreme Court of New Zealand | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Julien Chouinard]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Puisne Justice Supreme Court of Canada 1979–87 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Yves Fortier (lawyer)|Yves Fortier]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Permanent Court of Arbitration 1984&ndash;9, Ambassador UN 1988&ndash;92, Pres London Court of International Arbitration 1998&ndash;2001 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Susan Glazebrook]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | New Zealand | align="center" | Supreme Court of New Zealand | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Wilbur Jackett]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Chief Justice of the Federal Court of Canada 1971&ndash;79 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Gérard La Forest]] | align="center" | [[St John's College, Oxford|St John's]] | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Puisne Justice Supreme Court of Canada 1985–97 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Sherwood Lett]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Chief Justice Supreme Court of British Columbia 1955&ndash;64 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Ronald Martland]] | align="center" | [[Hertford College, Oxford|Hertford]] | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Puisne Justice Supreme Court of Canada 1958&ndash;82 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Henry Grattan Nolan|Henry G. Nolan]] | align="center" | | align="center" | | align="center" | Canada | align="center" | Prosecutor International Military Tribunal for the Far East 1946&ndash;8, Puisne Justice Supreme Court of Canada 1956&ndash;7 | align="center" | |- valign="top" | [[Roland Ritchie]] | align="center" | |